<setup>
  <selectFromSequence name="k" from="7" to="9" step="1"/>
  <selectFromSequence name="b" from="75" to="90" step="5"/>

  <function name="v" variable="t">$b-$k*t</function>
  <function name="s" variable="t">$b*t-$k*t^2/2</function>
  
</setup>  

<p>
  Suppose that a car is braking to a stop.  When it starts braking, its velocity is <m>$b</m> feet per second, and it brakes in such a way that its velocity decreases at a constant rate of <m>$k</m> feet per second per second.
</p>  

<p>
  <ol marker="a.">
    <li>
      <p>
        Find a formula for the car's velocity at an arbitrary time <m>t</m> between the time it starts braking and when its velocity reaches <m>0</m>. 
      </p>
      <p>
        <m>v(t) = </m> <answer>$v</answer> 
      </p>  
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        How long does it take for the car to come to a complete stop? 
      </p>
      <p>
        The car stops when <m>t = </m> <answer allowedErrorInNumbers="0.001" allowedErrorIsAbsolute>$b/$k</answer> seconds.
      </p>  
    </li>
    <li>
      <p> 
        How far does the car travel between the time it starts braking and when it stops?
      </p>  
      <p>
        The distance traveled while braking is <answer allowedErrorInNumbers="0.001" allowedErrorIsAbsolute>$$s($b/$k)</answer> with units <answer><choiceInput inline>
          <choice>?</choice>
          <choice>feet per second</choice>
          <choice credit="1">feet</choice>
          <choice>seconds</choice>
        </choiceInput></answer>.
      </p>  
    </li>  
  </ol>
</p>